io.spine.server.storage

Class MessageRecordSpec<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.server.storage.RecordSpec<I,R,R>
      • io.spine.server.storage.MessageRecordSpec<I,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of the record

    @Immutable
public final class MessageRecordSpec<I,R extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends RecordSpec<I,R,R>
    Instructs storage implementations on how to store a plain Protobuf message as a storage record.

    Defines the identifier column and the collection of the data columns to store along with the message record for further querying. Each column defines a way to calculate the stored value basing on the passed message.

    This specification is not well-suited for describing the storage of EntityRecords, as the values of their columns may be calculated from both the entity state and Entity instance attributes. See EntityRecordSpec for more details.

    See Also:
    EntityRecordSpec
